uotes":[],"military_service":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"First husband abandoned the family, then vanished","body":"Amanda's first husband Orlando Wilder — biological father of her two children Marion Eliza (born 1836) and Henry Harrison (born 1840) — last appeared in the 1840 Addison County Vermont census and then disappeared from all records. He had either abandoned the family or moved to Minnesota alone, leaving Amanda widow-like at age thirty with two young children. The disappearance was permanent."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Remarried Judge Joseph Hayward with three stepchildren","body":"Between 1840 and 1850 Amanda remarried — to Judge Joseph Hayward of Vermont (1796-1865). Hayward already had three children from his prior marriage (Asaph, Josephine, and Benjamin); they were Amanda's stepchildren, not her own biological children. The blended Wilder-Hayward household took shape across the 1840s, with Amanda raising her two Wilder children alongside her three Hayward stepchildren."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Daughter Marion married into Drake family","body":"Amanda's daughter Marion Eliza Wilder (born 1836) eventually married Drake — establishing the Wilder-Drake line that descended from the Hooker connection through Amanda's mother Lucinda Murray. Amanda's son Henry Harrison Wilder served as a private in the Civil War."},{"number":4,"category":"family","header":"Born Addison County VT 1810, died Vermont 1887","body":"Amanda Murray was born April 30, 1810 in Addison County Vermont and died December 9, 1887 in Vermont at age seventy-seven. Her two marriages with their distinct biological-vs-step parentage have been cross-checked against source records to establish the marriage order and parentage definitively."}],"slug":"amanda-hayward-1810"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}